                <note rend="inline" type="source">493.11 N 15/144: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-05-14T17:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 14, 1928—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 14—2:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>348. Your number 141, May 2, 6 p.m. Should Presbyterian Board not authorize
                    Patton to serve, I propose to designate as second American member of Joint
                    Commission, V. G. Lyman, retired from Standard Oil Company, notwithstanding a
                    member of Shanghai Municipal Council.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
